name: Fragment
title: Jordan 3 Retro Fragment
description:
Please Note: The clear heel tab does experience slight yellowing due to storage by the manufacturer. The Air Jordan 3 Fragment is the follow up to the very popular 2015 Air Jordan 1 collaboration. Fans waited patiently for Fragment’s founder Hiroshi Fujiwara to drop a new collaboration with Jordan Brand, after a slew of other collaborations with other entities such as Louis Vuitton, Anti-Social Social Club, and Pokemon. The Air Jordan 3 Fragment brings the lighting bolt brand back to a classic Jordan model.

Following Hiroshi Fujiwara’s love for simplistic motifs, the Air Jordan 3 Fragment comes dressed in white and black. The upper features a primarily white leather upper with a black full-grain leather mudguard. This collaboration replaces the Elephant print that typically appears on a Jordan 3 with plush black leather embossed with the Fragment lighting bolt logo. The sneaker’s white midsole has the colorway’s style code and release date printed in black text. To show true unison between the two brands, the Fragment’s lighting bolt logo appears behind a translucent Jumpman, in a similar fashion to August’s Fire Red Denim 3s.

The Air Jordan 3 Fragment dropped in September of 2020 for $200.

name: Fragment
title: Jordan Air Cadence Fragment
description:
The Air Jordan Air Cadence Fragment features a white, Particle Grey, Iron Grey and Smoke Grey premium suede and mesh upper with matching overlays. There is also dark gray synthetic fabric located at the heel. These Jordans have traditional Nike Air technology, a rubber outsole and a foam midsole.

The Air Jordan Air Cadence Fragment released in September of 2020 and retailed for $130.

name: Fragment
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Fragment
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Fragment is a retro-inspired collaborative sneaker by the Jordan Brand and Fragment design.\xa0

This high-top Air Jordan 1 sneaker features an all-leather upper with Retro Black toe color blocking accented by Royal Blue. Black appears on the forefoot, Swooshes, tongue, eyelets, and ankle collar, while Royal Blue dominates the heel and collar flaps. A Pristine White base on the toe and mid-panel completes the OG colorway. Other details include a Fragment Design logo etched on the lateral heel, the conventional ‘Wings’ logo on the outer collar flap, tongue branding, black laces, and toe box\xa0perforations. Underneath, a white midsole and Royal Blue rubber outsole complete the design. Each pair comes with an extra set of blue laces.

Our experts particularly love this sneaker’s colorway. The black/white/Royal Blue color blocking on the leather upper give this sneaker a timeless look. The Jordan 1 Retro Fragment was made available on December 27th, 2014, retailing at $185.

name: Fragment
title: Jordan XXXV Fragment
description:
The Air Jordan XXXXV Fragment comes as a multicolored shoe that features black, white, and blue as the main colorways.

This Fragment Air Jordan XXXXV sneaker features a combination of leather and synthetic materials on its upper. It draws inspiration from Fragment Design's color scheme, incorporating a blend of blue, white, as well as black. The heel of this sneaker displays a Thunderbolt emblem, while the Jumpman logo is present on the tongue, quarter panel, as well as on its outsole. The model is completed with a tricolor midsole, which adds a finishing touch to its design. Additionally, the shoe is equipped with a white lacing system that enhances its appearance.

The upper of this shoe relies on a mesh-based shell\xa0upper that improves its breathability, which is the feature that our experts found attractive on this sneaker. The Air Jordan XXXXV Fragment was advised to sell at about $195 when it released on October 28th, 2020.

name: Fragment Friends and Family
title: Jordan 1 Retro Fragment Friends and Family

name: Fragment x Travis Scott
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Fragment x Travis Scott
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Fragment Design x Travis Scott nods to the original 2016 Air Jordan 1 Fragment with its simple color blocking. It features a smooth white leather upper with black and royal blue leather overlays. From there, a signature reversed Swoosh and yellowed soles add a Cactus Jack flair to the classic silhouette.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Fragment Design x Travis Scott released in August of 2021 and retailed for $150.

name: Fragment x Travis Scott
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Fragment x Travis Scott
description:
The Air Jordan 1 High OG SP Fragment Design x Travis Scott fragment draws inspiration from a Jordan 1 Royal press sample from 1985 with its white and blue tumbled leather upper. Similar to previous Travis Scott Jordan 1s, signature reverse Swooshes and hidden stash pockets in the collar add on to the classic design. From there, both Travis Scott's Cactus Jack and Fragment logos are debossed in black on the heel wrap.

The Air Jordan 1 High OG SP Fragment Design x Travis Scott released in July of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Infrared
title: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Infrared features a tonal grey Durabuck upper with black TPU mesh inserts, tech straps, and heel tabs. Hits of Infrared on the lacing system and woven Jordan Flight tongue label add a sharp contrast to the neutral-toned base. From there, a white sole with visible Air units completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Infrared released in June of 2022 and retailed for $200.

name: Infrared (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS)
description:
Built in grade school sizing, the Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS) adds some color to an otherwise neutral colorway of the vintage silhouette.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS) is built on a dark grey nubuck upper with black accents on the quarter panel netting, structural wings, and Jumpman-branded heel piece. Sitting atop the dark grey base is a lighter shade of grey forefoot overlay, while touches of Infrared appear on the molded eyelets and woven Jumpman tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an exposed Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of the two-tone midsole.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (GS) was released in June 2022 and retailed for $160.

name: Black Infrared (2019)
title: Jordan 6 Retro Black Infrared (2019)
description: Make sure your head isn’t in the beam while trying to grab the Jordan 6 Retro Black Infrared (2019). This AJ6 come with a black upper, black midsole plus red accents, and a translucent sole. These sneakers released in February 2019 and retailed for $200. This silhouette is a must cop, so purchase them on StockX now.

name: Black Valor Blue
title: Jordan Legacy 312 Low Black Valor Blue

name: SoleFly
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP SoleFly
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Solefly draws inspiration from the carnivorous wildlife of the Florida Everglades. Smothered in ferocious patterns, beige debossed toe wrap and heel wrap pop against a black and red premium suede upper. From there, SoleFly and Air Jordan logos on the heel tabs add a custom feel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Solefly released in December of 2021 and retailed for $150.

name: First Class Flight
title: Jordan 1 Retro High First Class Flight
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High First Class Flight features a white, black, and Dynamic Yellow leather upper with perforations dotting the top of the toebox. From there, special UPC barcode stamps adorn the lateral heel of the shoe, followed by black "Nike Air" lettering against a yellow background at the tongue and more yellow on the collar, with both white and Dynamic Yellow "Swooshes" on either side to complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Retro High First Class Flight released in September 2019 and retailed for $160.

name: Pink Glaze Cactus Flower (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Pink Glaze Cactus Flower (Women's)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Cauliflower W is a women’s sneaker by Nike with a dominant pink hue throughout its design.

The High Zoom Air Air Jordan 1 features pink overlays on a white tumble leather base. The pink hue is along the ankle flaps and in the overlays on the mid-foot, forefoot and lower heel, black leather around the collar of the model, and white on the toe boxes and quarter panelling. The shoe has an orange Swoosh and the overlay running along the laces has a loose piece at the top.

The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Cauliflower W was released on 23rd January 2021, retailing at $140.

name: Flipped Infrared
title: Jordan 36 Low Flipped Infrared
description: The Air Jordan 36 Flipped Infrared 23 is a highly anticipated release from the iconic sneaker brand. The shoe features a sleek black and white colorway with pops of vibrant Infrared 23 accents. The upper is constructed with a mix of breathable mesh and durable leather, providing both comfort and support. The shoe also boasts a responsive Zoom Air unit in the forefoot for added cushioning during high-impact activities. The Air Jordan 36 Flipped Infrared 23 was released on May 19, 2022, with a retail price of $185. This shoe is a must-have for sneaker enthusiasts and basketball players alike, offering both style and performance in one package.

name: Infrared (PS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared (PS)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared PS is a modification of the retro design of Air Jordan 4, featuring "infrared" properties.

The upper of the Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared PS is made from black nubuck with leather eyelets that feature contrasting crimson accents. Its quarter panel is made from meshed material, while its full-length midsole is made of foam material. On the exterior of the Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared PS, the white Jumpman logo is on the tongue, as well as the model heel panel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Infrared PS debuted on June 15, 2020. At the time of its debut, the price of the shoe was $200.

name: Take Flight (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Take Flight (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Take Flight GS was inspired by Peter Moore and comes in a white/Bright Crimson-Blue Hero colorway. This grade-schooler-sized sneaker is adorned with white leather on the mid-panel and toe box sections.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Take Flight GS appears in a cloud digital print that sits atop an outerspace-like fusion of red, blue, and black hues covering the heel, front quarter, eyestay, and toe box sections. The shoe features Swoosh intersections, revealing the words "Take Flight" printed in a red-and-blue color scheme. Also, a doubled-up Jumpman logo is affixed to the tongue with the metallic silver Air Jordan "Wings" logo on the black laces and lateral collar, delivering a contrasting scheme.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Take Flight GS was released on February 10th, 2021, at a retail price of $100.
